The Director-General, National Youth Service Corps (NYSC),  Brig.-Gen. Shuaibu Ibrahim, has warned corps members against unauthorised   and late night journeys. He gave the warning on Friday night in Benin when he visited eight corps members who were involved in an accident and are receiving treatment at the University of Benin Teaching Hospital (UBTH). The corps members were on their way to Port Harcourt from the orientation camp in Ekiti State when they had an auto crash on the Benin bypass on Friday night. “I have always warned against late night travels. Please, corps members, break your journeys if it is late,” he said. While commending the management of UBTH for taking care of the corps members, he  assured that  the corps was working with security agencies to ensure safety of  corps members across the country. He assured families of the corps members that they would not be abandoned. NYSC DG visits corps members accident victims, warns against unauthorised journey NYSC stops corps members from unauthorized journeys NYSC to corps members: Be security conscious